entry.title: Immigration Backlashes Spread Around the World
entry.content: The collapse of the Netherlands’ government is the latest sign of discord as immigration surges to record levels, fueling populism.

entry.title: From Prison to New York City Council
entry.content: As a teenager, Yusef Salaam was wrongfully imprisoned as one of the Central Park Five. Now, he is preparing to take a seat on the New York City Council.

entry.title: The Professor Helping Guide Billions in Climate Spending
entry.content: Jesse Jenkins’s ZERO Lab says that faster upgrades for the power grid are essential to cutting emissions.

entry.title: The Victims of a Russian Strike on a Pizzeria: Ukrainian Author, Teenage Twins, Ex-U.S. Marine
entry.content: The June attack on Kramatorsk, eastern Ukraine, killed at least 13 civilians and an unknown number of soldiers in a restaurant that was a social hub.
